00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:39,180
 That's a great passage for seasons of waiting, by the way.

352
00:22:39,180 --> 00:22:41,620
 But notice what Peter is doing here.

353
00:22:41,620 --> 00:22:43,740
 He's saying, "Remember."

354
00:22:43,740 --> 00:22:46,180
 He's saying, "I'm writing to you so you would remember."

355
00:22:46,180 --> 00:22:48,820
 He's like, "Recall the words of the prophets."

356
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:51,180
 He's saying, "Don't forget this.

357
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:57,140
 Don't allow fear and anxiety to strip away from you faith, and hope, and an active anticipation

358
00:22:57,140 --> 00:23:01,720
 of change, and the prophetic stance that waiting should place inside of you.

359
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:07,380
 Don't allow the fear to cause you to forget.

360
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:10,380
 Remember what it is that I have done."

361
00:23:10,380 --> 00:23:13,320
 Some of you, I want to say it this way.

362
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:19,580
 Some of you are listening far more to what the wait is saying to you than what the Word

363
00:23:19,580 --> 00:23:22,300
 is teaching you.

364
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:24,180
 Come on, church.

365
00:23:24,180 --> 00:23:30,140
 Some of you are just way more in tune with what the wait is screaming at you than what

366
00:23:30,140 --> 00:23:34,220
 the Word is whispering to you.

367
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:39,360
 May we not forget what it is that the Lord has poured out upon His people.

368
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:45,500
 Let us not forget what He has done in our past, and let us see that as a deposit to

369
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:48,300
 the faithfulness of His goodness in the present.

370
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:49,300
 Amen?

371
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,300
 That's the first thing.

372
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:52,220
 Here's the second thing found in verse 1.

373
00:23:52,220 --> 00:23:55,340
 "The Lord is my light and my salvation.

374
00:23:55,340 --> 00:23:57,100
 Whom should I fear?

375
00:23:57,100 --> 00:23:59,340
 The Lord is the stronghold of my life.

376
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:02,300
 Of whom should I be afraid?"

377
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:05,820
 David starts the psalm with one word in Hebrew.

378
00:24:05,820 --> 00:24:10,100
 Obviously, that's what would happen, but this particular word that he chooses is very, very

379
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:11,100
 important.

380
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:12,900
 He chooses the word "Lord."

381
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:17,460
 It will show up in your English translations as L-O-R-D in capital letters.

382
00:24:17,460 --> 00:24:22,340
 It's the sacred name of the Jewish personal understanding of God.

383
00:24:22,340 --> 00:24:27,300
 There were a number of names for God that David in the Hebrew could have chosen to start

384
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,300
 the psalm.

