00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:32,540
 Rahim being one of the other ones that is very popular, particularly in his time.

386
00:24:32,540 --> 00:24:39,180
 But he chooses this Yahweh word that we've come to say Yahweh, which means "I am."

387
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:41,620
 It means literally, "I am that I am."

388
00:24:41,620 --> 00:24:46,980
 You might remember that this was first spoken over the Jewish people by Moses, by God, at

389
00:24:46,980 --> 00:24:48,740
 the burning bush with Moses.

390
00:24:48,740 --> 00:24:51,440
 Moses asks God, "Who are you?"

391
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:56,580
 He wants to know who this God is that is coming to deliver His people, and God personally

392
00:24:56,580 --> 00:24:58,940
 reveals Himself as this Yahweh.

393
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:02,020
 He says, "I am that I am."

394
00:25:02,020 --> 00:25:06,460
 The word "I am" is in the present continuous tense.

395
00:25:06,460 --> 00:25:11,520
 It's the idea that this God is a God that's present.

396
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:15,180
 This is really important because I think what David's doing right at the beginning of the

397
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:18,580
 psalm is saying, "Here's where our hope is."

398
00:25:18,580 --> 00:25:24,340
 Yes, it's important that you remember what God has done in your past and hold on to that

399
00:25:24,340 --> 00:25:25,740
 in your future.

400
00:25:25,740 --> 00:25:29,220
 That's one way to deal with the anxiety that's in your mind.

401
00:25:29,220 --> 00:25:30,220
 But here's the thing.

402
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:34,460
 You do not worship a God of your past.

403
00:25:34,460 --> 00:25:39,100
 The God that we worship is the God of the here and the now.

404
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:43,220
 And so his starting point is, "I am" is with us.

405
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:45,380
 "I am" is present.

406
00:25:45,380 --> 00:25:47,580
 That He's the same yesterday, today, and forever.

407
00:25:47,580 --> 00:25:54,300
 That His very context is this revelation that He is the mighty I am.

408
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:58,260
 He's not, "I was good, therefore remember it."

409
00:25:58,260 --> 00:26:02,280
 He is, "I am good in the here and now."

410
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:04,580
 He's not, "I was your healer."

411
00:26:04,580 --> 00:26:07,000
 He is, "I am your healer."

412
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:10,180
 He's not, "I was someone who's spoken to your life before."

413
00:26:10,180 --> 00:26:15,060
 He is someone, "I am who is speaking into your life now."

414
00:26:15,060 --> 00:26:18,780
 So it feels like, you know, maybe on the one side that David might be contradicting himself

415
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:19,780
 here.

416
00:26:19,780 --> 00:26:20,780
 He's not.

417
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:21,780
 He's saying, "We should look back.

418
00:26:21,780 --> 00:26:22,780
 We should remember."

419
00:26:22,780 --> 00:26:27,340
 It's a biblical principle to remember God and to hold that memory in the seasons of

420
00:26:27,340 --> 00:26:28,340
 waiting.

421
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:32,900
 But he's like this, "You've got to be really careful that in a season of waiting, you don't

422
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:36,540
 end up worshiping and I was God."

423
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:37,540
 Come on church.

424
00:26:37,540 --> 00:26:40,940
 "You've got to be careful that your season of waiting, you don't end up worshiping and

425
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:42,140
 I was God."

426
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:44,540
 I have so many conversations like this with people.

427
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:49,980
 "Oh man, God was awesome to me in 1985."

428
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:52,860
 Or "God was awesome to me two years ago."

429
00:26:52,860 --> 00:26:58,220
 God was great to me when I was in this place or with these people or in that community.

430
00:26:58,220 --> 00:27:01,660
 And absolutely, we celebrate those moments.

431
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:06,460
 Absolutely, like David says in verse two, we look back on that to remind ourselves of

432
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:07,740
 him in the way.

433
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:12,860
 But what David's really trying to stress to his church is that it's not about worshiping

434
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:14,800
 some thing of the past.

435
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,580
 We worship the great I am.

436
00:27:16,580 --> 00:27:21,420
 He doesn't reveal himself as I was who I was.

437
00:27:21,420 --> 00:27:25,660
 Nor does he reveal himself as I will be what I will be.

438
00:27:25,660 --> 00:27:30,060
 He reveals himself as I am that I am.

439
00:27:30,060 --> 00:27:34,740
 Your God, no matter what it might feel like in the waiting, is fighting battles right

440
00:27:34,740 --> 00:27:37,260
 here, right now.

441
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:42,140
 This is why then David goes on and says, "The Lord, this Yahweh, this great I am, is my

442
00:27:42,140 --> 00:27:45,140
 light, my salvation.

443
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:48,100
 The Lord is the stronghold of my life."

444
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:49,100
 This is really beautiful.

445
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:52,060
 David's doing something really important and we can't miss this.

446
00:27:52,060 --> 00:27:55,740
 David's not like a professor with some board, you know, whiteboard.

447
00:27:55,740 --> 00:27:59,780
 And he's like, "Here's some doctrine you need to know about God and believe, regardless

448
00:27:59,780 --> 00:28:01,780
 of whether you've encountered this in him before."

449
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:06,420
 No, he says over his people, "You've got to understand that I have a personal relationship

450
00:28:06,420 --> 00:28:07,980
 with this God.

451
00:28:07,980 --> 00:28:10,280
 That he is my light.

452
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:12,560
 He is my salvation.

453
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,900
 He is the stronghold of my life.

454
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:18,500
 I'm not just trying to tell you that he is the light."

455
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:19,500
 Notice this in the scripture.

456
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:23,180
 He doesn't say he is the light, although he is.

457
00:28:23,180 --> 00:28:26,680
 He doesn't say he's the salvation, although he is.

458
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,900
 He says, "No, this is about me.

459
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:32,980
 This is my personal encounter, my personal testimony."

460
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:37,900
 Like the testimonies we just heard in this room a moment ago, David is writing to Israel

461
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:42,260
 and he's saying, "In seasons of waiting, let me tell you what I've encountered.

462
00:28:42,260 --> 00:28:45,500
 I'm not trying to teach you something here that I haven't journeyed through.

463
00:28:45,500 --> 00:28:49,780
 I'm not trying to speak something into you that's a doctrine that you should believe

464
00:28:49,780 --> 00:28:50,780
 without thinking."

465
00:28:50,780 --> 00:28:54,540
 No, he's like, "This is my personal experience.

466
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:58,380
 I have found him in the waiting.

467
00:28:58,380 --> 00:29:06,560
 Where I have felt anxious and fearful, where my mind was spiraling, he became my light,

468
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:09,260
 my salvation, my stronghold."

469
00:29:09,260 --> 00:29:15,260
 It's fascinating to me that the three words he chooses here are words that speak specifically

470
00:29:15,260 --> 00:29:21,580
 into this context of fear and anxiety that is the backdrop to the first three passages.

471
00:29:21,580 --> 00:29:24,500
 He says, "He is my light."

472
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:30,220
 The number one thing that anxiety or fear will do is cause you to retreat to darkness.

473
00:29:30,220 --> 00:29:36,620
 Fear and anxiety always makes us want to flight away, to hide, to crawl back into bed and

474
00:29:36,620 --> 00:29:41,380
 throw the covers over us and hope the day goes away.

475
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:48,220
 Fear and anxiety drives us to dark places, places of depression or sadness or even at

476
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:51,420
 worst case, to places like suicide.

477
00:29:51,420 --> 00:29:56,340
 Fear and anxiety drives us out of the light and into the shadows.

478
00:29:56,340 --> 00:30:00,540
 And I love the fact that David goes, "You want to know who the I am is for me.

479
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:03,780
 He was my light when everything was dark.

480
00:30:03,780 --> 00:30:08,140
 When I was struggling with fear and I wanted to run, when I felt darkness around me, when

481
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:14,420
 I was sad and entrenched in depression, I recognized that he magnified his spirit in

482
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:22,020
 my life and he became my light and light always extinguishes darkness."

483
00:30:22,020 --> 00:30:25,060
 He then says, "He's my salvation."

484
00:30:25,060 --> 00:30:29,860
 It's easy for us in our New Testament thinking as the New Testament church today, whenever

485
00:30:29,860 --> 00:30:34,100
 we read the word salvation in the Old Testament, our minds immediately go, don't they, to the

486
00:30:34,100 --> 00:30:39,380
 cross and to Jesus and to salvation of sin and the brokenness of all that and the liberation

487
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,200
 that comes through our brokenness with Christ.

488
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,660
 And of course, that is the story.

489
00:30:42,660 --> 00:30:47,260
 But when David's using the word salvation here, he's taking a Hebrew word that means

490
00:30:47,260 --> 00:30:50,460
 rescuer or deliverer.

491
00:30:50,460 --> 00:30:56,060
 And one of the things that fear and anxiety always does to us is it binds us in chains.

492
00:30:56,060 --> 00:30:58,100
 It chains our thinking.

493
00:30:58,100 --> 00:30:59,700
 It chains our hope.

494
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:02,060
 It chains our energy.

495
00:31:02,060 --> 00:31:07,100
 And we suddenly feel captive to our own thoughts, captive to our environment, captive to the

496
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:10,900
 circumstances that seem to be spiraling around us.

497
00:31:10,900 --> 00:31:15,060
 Fear and anxiety will lock you up.

498
00:31:15,060 --> 00:31:19,140
 And so David says, "He is my rescuer, my deliverer."

499
00:31:19,140 --> 00:31:23,140
 I think another way he could have wrote it, "He broke my chains.

500
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:26,780
 He freed my mind from the pit that it was in.

501
00:31:26,780 --> 00:31:32,540
 He helped me to think better, have more hope, hold on to him in the hardest of times.

502
00:31:32,540 --> 00:31:33,540
 He rescued me.

503
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:34,620
 He delivered me.

504
00:31:34,620 --> 00:31:38,100
 He broke the chains."

505
00:31:38,100 --> 00:31:41,200
 And then he says, "He's the stronghold of my life."

506
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,200
 This is really cool.

507
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:43,420
 Notice what he does here.

508
00:31:43,420 --> 00:31:48,080
 The word stronghold here in the Hebrew was actually a military term.

509
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:50,420
 It was a military picture.

510
00:31:50,420 --> 00:31:54,540
 Oftentimes what would happen for the king when they were on a battlefield is that they

511
00:31:54,540 --> 00:31:58,140
 would be in the middle and maybe the armies are rushing towards them.

512
00:31:58,140 --> 00:32:04,700
 His best officers would place themselves in a circle around him, hold up their shields

513
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:11,020
 so that the arrows and the attack won't affect or hurt the king in the middle.

514
00:32:11,020 --> 00:32:14,020
 That was known as a stronghold.

515
00:32:14,020 --> 00:32:15,100
 Strongholds could also be physical.

516
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:18,820
 So they could be the people around helping, but it could also be physical.

517
00:32:18,820 --> 00:32:25,900
 So in wars sometimes they built literal strongholds with walls to wall out the enemy so that anybody

518
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:31,040
 inside the building were surrounded by safety and security.

519
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:35,620
 So notice David takes this and he's like, "I want you to understand that when fear and

520
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:41,420
 anxiety is at work in me, that anxiety comes because my enemy has surrounded me."

521
00:32:41,420 --> 00:32:42,920
 Remember this, verse three?

522
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:47,220
 He said, "My enemy has surrounded me so I feel anxiety."

523
00:32:47,220 --> 00:32:49,220
 You want to know one of the ways I deal with that anxiety?

524
00:32:49,220 --> 00:32:54,780
 I realize that there's something else surrounding me more.

525
00:32:54,780 --> 00:33:01,420
 He says, "The Lord, my Lord, is the stronghold of my life.

526
00:33:01,420 --> 00:33:07,220
 He's the one who is protecting me, walling around me, ensuring that the fiery arrows

527
00:33:07,220 --> 00:33:09,660
 of the enemy can never impact me.

528
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:16,660
 Yes, it may well be true that my enemies have surrounded me, but God has surrounded me first.

529
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:20,060
 But God is the immediacy of what is around me.

530
00:33:20,060 --> 00:33:25,140
 And so look, anything in this life could surround me as well, but it is the Yahweh, it is my

531
00:33:25,140 --> 00:33:28,700
 God who surrounds me and fights battles and He's the one.

532
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:34,940
 And so I might be in a field with all my enemies, but I feel safe and protected because I am

533
00:33:34,940 --> 00:33:37,900
 surrounded by Him."

534
00:33:37,900 --> 00:33:43,380
 That beautiful song that Promise and the team have written here at the Vine, "He surrounds

535
00:33:43,380 --> 00:33:46,500
 and He upholds me."

536
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:50,140
 This is the cry of David in Psalm 27.

537
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:55,180
 He's like, "You want to know how to beat the battle in your mind that is happening with

538
00:33:55,180 --> 00:33:59,500
 anxiety and fear in seasons of waiting?

539
00:33:59,500 --> 00:34:03,100
 Know that He will bring light where the fear is bringing darkness.

540
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:07,580
 Know that He is going to rescue you where you feel like you're in chains.

541
00:34:07,580 --> 00:34:15,540
 Know that no matter how the enemy might try to surround you, He surrounds you more."

542
00:34:15,540 --> 00:34:18,100
 Surrounding battles for you.

543
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:24,340
 This is very personal for David and this passage is very personal for me.

544
00:34:24,340 --> 00:34:30,180
 This is something that I am not only have struggled with all my life, but it's something

545
00:34:30,180 --> 00:34:33,380
 I'm currently struggling with now.

546
00:34:33,380 --> 00:34:36,180
 Anxiety has been something that's been in my family.

547
00:34:36,180 --> 00:34:39,500
 It's been a part of the generations of my family.

548
00:34:39,500 --> 00:34:43,300
 My great-grandfather had it, my grandfather, my father.

549
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:48,860
 I struggle with it, my siblings also in different seasons, in different ways struggle with it.

550
00:34:48,860 --> 00:34:52,220
 Anxiety is present for the Gardner family.

551
00:34:52,220 --> 00:34:55,500
 And I go through seasons of anxiety usually when I'm in a season of waiting.

552
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:56,980
 And I'm in a season of waiting right now.

553
00:34:56,980 --> 00:35:00,380
 I've been praying for something for quite some time now that hasn't come through for

554
00:35:00,380 --> 00:35:04,900
 me and I don't want to share what that is, but I do want to let you know that this means

555
00:35:04,900 --> 00:35:09,220
 something to me because I'm really struggling with anxiety.

556
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:12,260
 It's something that's been building for me in the last couple of months.

557
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:17,700
 Something that really had a big impact on me in the run up to Christmas just back a

558
00:35:17,700 --> 00:35:19,580
 few weeks ago.

559
00:35:19,580 --> 00:35:25,420
 And when anxiety is at work in my life, I want to run, I want to get away, I want to

560
00:35:25,420 --> 00:35:26,940
 retreat.

561
00:35:26,940 --> 00:35:30,260
 And I was praying about three weeks ago about this.

562
00:35:30,260 --> 00:35:33,860
 I was so anxious at night that I wasn't sleeping well, dealing with insomnia.

563
00:35:33,860 --> 00:35:36,460
 And I'm there praying.

564
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:41,140
 And as I'm praying, I felt like the Holy Spirit say this to me, "Andrew, don't you realize

565
00:35:41,140 --> 00:35:43,300
 that I'm your light?

566
00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:48,260
 That I am your rescuer, your deliverer.

567
00:35:48,260 --> 00:35:52,380
 Don't you know that I am your stronghold?"

568
00:35:52,380 --> 00:35:56,740
 And I felt this peace flood over me in a very practical way.

569
00:35:56,740 --> 00:36:03,260
 And I suddenly felt this new perspective on something that I was struggling and wrestling

570
00:36:03,260 --> 00:36:04,260
 with.

571
00:36:04,260 --> 00:36:07,980
 I'm still waiting for the thing I'm praying about to happen and to come through for me.

572
00:36:07,980 --> 00:36:12,780
 But I know that the anxiety has been processed and has reduced.

573
00:36:12,780 --> 00:36:15,620
 Still a battle for me, but it is something that is being reduced.

574
00:36:15,620 --> 00:36:21,340
 And I can stand before you today and say this, "He is my light.

575
00:36:21,340 --> 00:36:25,460
 He is my rescuer, and I need him to be my stronghold."

576
00:36:25,460 --> 00:36:32,420
 And David says, "The waiting is hard, and anxiety and fear will be there with you in

577
00:36:32,420 --> 00:36:34,340
 it.

578
00:36:34,340 --> 00:36:37,380
 Remember what he's done for you in the past.

579
00:36:37,380 --> 00:36:40,060
 Don't allow fear to wipe the memory.

580
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:44,260
 Don't allow fear to create spiritual amnesia in you.

581
00:36:44,260 --> 00:36:48,540
 Hold on to what he's done, because it's a deposit for his faithfulness now.

582
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:51,760
 But also don't worship a God of the past.

583
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:56,420
 Worship a God who's here with you, fighting those battles, conscious with you, walking

584
00:36:56,420 --> 00:37:02,340
 with you, the one who can be the light and the salvation and the stronghold in this moment."

585
00:37:02,340 --> 00:37:09,820
 This is why David then says with all confidence before his people, "Whom should I fear?

586
00:37:09,820 --> 00:37:13,240
 Of whom should I be afraid?

587
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:15,580
 Because he is the mighty I am."

588
00:37:15,580 --> 00:37:16,580
 Amen?

589
00:37:16,580 --> 00:37:19,100
 Can I pray for us?

590
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:32,100
 Maybe you can stand with me and I'm going to pray.

591
00:37:32,100 --> 00:37:39,140
 Father, we stand before you as a community really grateful, grateful that David has such

592
00:37:39,140 --> 00:37:42,260
 honesty in his writing.

593
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:45,780
 He's able to write so confidently in these first three verses because he's done some

594
00:37:45,780 --> 00:37:48,260
 battle in the past.

595
00:37:48,260 --> 00:37:53,780
 A man who understood anxiety and fear and felt it acutely.

596
00:37:53,780 --> 00:37:57,700
 A man who could process where that was coming from.

597
00:37:57,700 --> 00:38:03,740
 And a man who gives two very practical ways for his people to deal with it.

598
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:08,940
 Lord, I want to pray for anyone here in the season of waiting that they're in right now.

599
00:38:08,940 --> 00:38:14,260
 And maybe that season of waiting is creating anxiety and fear within them.

600
00:38:14,260 --> 00:38:22,620
 Father, I pray, first of all, that you would lift spiritual amnesia in the name of Jesus.

601
00:38:22,620 --> 00:38:26,020
 Lord, where fear has created forgetfulness.

602
00:38:26,020 --> 00:38:33,580
 Lord, I want to pray that you would now bring a spirit of recollection, a spirit of remembering,

603
00:38:33,580 --> 00:38:39,060
 a spirit of hope that is birthed by the, "Ah, yes.

604
00:38:39,060 --> 00:38:40,940
 God did do that for me before.

605
00:38:40,940 --> 00:38:42,620
 How did I forget that?

606
00:38:42,620 --> 00:38:44,580
 How did I not remember that?"

607
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:50,540
 Lord, I pray that you would stir friends to come around other friends and say, "Don't

608
00:38:50,540 --> 00:38:51,540
 forget that God did this.

609
00:38:51,540 --> 00:38:52,940
 I remember when you told me this.

610
00:38:52,940 --> 00:38:55,980
 Have you forgotten the testimony you told me yourself?"

611
00:38:55,980 --> 00:39:02,780
 Lord, I pray you would stir such amazing memory amongst your people that the hold that the

612
00:39:02,780 --> 00:39:09,060
 enemy has with anxiety and fear on the people of God in the season of waiting will be lifted

613
00:39:09,060 --> 00:39:12,780
 in the name of Jesus.

614
00:39:12,780 --> 00:39:15,500
 But as David has shown us, we do not worship the "I was God."

615
00:39:15,500 --> 00:39:21,940
 And so, Lord, we stand before you in this moment saying, "You are the great I am."

616
00:39:21,940 --> 00:39:27,100
 And Lord, we pray for the light to shine to the dark places for those that are struggling

617
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:28,260
 at this time.

618
00:39:28,260 --> 00:39:35,900
 Lord, we pray for your rescuing, the breaking of chains in the name of Jesus.

619
00:39:35,900 --> 00:39:37,220
 I feel like this for the 11.

620
00:39:37,220 --> 00:39:41,060
 If that's for you, I just want to invite you as our eyes are closed just to open your hands.

621
00:39:41,060 --> 00:39:45,380
 You know that there's some part of your mind, there's some part of your emotions, there's

622
00:39:45,380 --> 00:39:50,100
 some part of your even physicality that you know is chained at the moment.

623
00:39:50,100 --> 00:39:56,100
 And maybe it's been chained by fear or anxiety or the worry of what's ahead or the worry

624
00:39:56,100 --> 00:40:00,300
 for your children or the worry for your work or whatever it is, but you recognize that

625
00:40:00,300 --> 00:40:04,500
 there is this binding, you've been bound by something.

626
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:10,060
 Lord, for those whose hands are open in this moment, I pray now in the name of Jesus that

627
00:40:10,060 --> 00:40:13,060
 the name of Jesus breaks chains.

628
00:40:13,060 --> 00:40:18,140
 And I want to pray for that rescue and that deliverance that only Jesus Christ can do

629
00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:22,780
 for those that feel bound in this season of waiting.

630
00:40:22,780 --> 00:40:27,140
 And Father, you are our stronghold.

631
00:40:27,140 --> 00:40:35,380
 You are the God that surrounds us, who is between us and the surrounding of our enemies.

632
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:39,100
 And I feel as I'm praying, some of you in this room, you're in a season of waiting where

633
00:40:39,100 --> 00:40:43,580
 it feels like the enemy is really close.

634
00:40:43,580 --> 00:40:48,820
 The anxiety and the overwhelming sense is very pertinent to you.

635
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:54,780
 The Lord would say, I am closer to you than the enemies around you.

636
00:40:54,780 --> 00:40:58,980
 I will surround and I will uphold you.

637
00:40:58,980 --> 00:41:02,660
 I will strengthen you with my mighty right hand.

638
00:41:02,660 --> 00:41:06,140
 I am fighting battles that you are not even aware of.

639
00:41:06,140 --> 00:41:10,300
 And I am, I am.

640
00:41:10,300 --> 00:41:14,980
 So Lord, I want to pray that you would bless those that are desperately in need of a God

641
00:41:14,980 --> 00:41:20,820
 who fights battles, that they would leave here today knowing that you surround them

642
00:41:20,820 --> 00:41:25,060
 and that if you are for them, as Paul would write many years later, who can be against

643
00:41:25,060 --> 00:41:26,060
 us?

644
00:41:26,060 --> 00:41:33,020
 So Lord, we thank you that this season of waiting, while it might bring those uncomfortable

645
00:41:33,020 --> 00:41:37,100
 emotions, that we are not left alone.

646
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:42,660
 May the God of the past be the deposit of faithfulness now.

647
00:41:42,660 --> 00:41:53,060
 And may the breaker of chains, the provider of light and the surrounder of power and hope

648
00:41:53,060 --> 00:41:54,660
 be with you now and forever.

649
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:57,180
 In Jesus' name, everyone says, Amen.

650
00:41:57,180 --> 00:42:07,180
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

